commandserver
Class ClientRecord

java.lang.Object
  commandserver.ClientRecord

public class ClientRecord
extends java.lang.Object

ClientRecord - the records in the database. Includes all fields associated with a single client, except for it's uid, which the record is keyed by in the database.

Author:
W. Taff and P. Salevski

Parameters:

setClientInbox

public void setClientInbox(java.lang.String message)
Allows server to write message to client inbox. Only servers shall write to the client inbox. Read by clients to ascertain their instructions from server.

Parameters:
hostID - - uid_host of the host of interest
message - - String of message FROM server TO client.

setClientStatus

public void setClientStatus(java.lang.String message)
Allows client to set their status in status box of record. Only clients shall write their status to their status box. Read by the server to ascertain status of the client.

Parameters:
hostID - - uid_host of the host of interest
status - - String of status value of host.
